The answer is: Typical GAN architectures for text-to-image synthesis can be grouped into four major categories according to their focus: Semantic Enhancement GANs (aiming to improve the semantic relevance of the generated images to the input text), Resolution Enhancement GANs (focusing on generating high-resolution images), Diversity Enhancement GANs (enhancing the variety of generated images), and Motion Enhancement GANs (introducing motion
159.answer:
Semantic Enhancement GANs: DC-GANs, MC-GAN
Resolution Enhancement GANs: StackGANs, AttnGAN, HDGAN
Diversity Enhancement GANs: AC-GAN, TAC-GAN etc.
Motion Enhancement GAGs: T2S, T2V, StoryGAN
